                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18241028-27-victim308 t18241028-27-viclabel147"></join>, was living in my house. The prisoner came and said, he was sent from my sister's to fetch some flower-pots, a hair broom and some other articles which I gave him, with the bed furniture and carpet; he went away with them. I did not see him again till he was taken into custody; on the 27th or 28th of October; he might be in my sight about ten minutes; and when I saw him again I was quite certain of his person; I had seen him once before. My sister's name is 
               <persName id="t18241028-27-person311">
                  Mary 
                  Ann Hamilton
               <interp inst="t18241028-27-person311" type="surname" value="Ann Hamilton"></interp>
